President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring the week of August 10-16, 2014, as National Health Center Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of health centers in providing quality, affordable healthcare to all individuals, regardless of their socioeconomic status or background. The proclamation recognizes the role of health centers in connecting patients with community resources and helping them access coverage through the Affordable Care Act. It also emphasizes the investments made in health centers to expand their services and reduce disparities in care. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate National Health Center Week by visiting their local health centers and exploring the programs they offer to promote health and well-being.